column4: can someone please help? I used alien to convert vmwareworkstation into deb and installed it. bBut when I run /usr/bin/vmware-config.pl it returns an error message in the end
aliening vmware is probably not a good idea
aliening small things here and there, probably harmless, but vmware is definitely not something you want to do that on
you have to tell us what the error is, and use pastebin please
sounds like it is saying that the package's control file has two entries for original maintainer
My noobness makes me have no idea what that means
it is an error I have never seen and I can't begin to think of how to fix it, I mean maybe some dpkg -r --force-all package kind of thing might do it, very funny error
if it helps: it started after I installed vmware with an aliened .deb package
yeah bad idea
try removing that package
I cant...it just tells me to apt-get -f install
lol
it must tell you more than that
since i installed it with dpkg -i i did a dpkg -r vmwareworkstation
and it just tells me that duplicate maintainer thing
try sudo dpkg -r --force-all vmwareworkstation
it is likely that ubuntu has an old version of azureus
ubuntu is not too big on latest applications
why is that??
just aren't

no he wasn't, he though he had found something that I hadn't seen and tried to act like he had achieved something but failed to realize that < 48 kb file recovery is what he found which is nearly useless
yeah I just saw it...but its ok. make peace =)
